1010
Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before you today to plea guilty to the offense of affray. I am truly remorseful for the events that unfolded at the bar and the discomfort I caused to those present.

Following the revelation of my boyfriend's infidelity, I found myself overwhelmed with anger and pain. In an impulsive decision, I went to the bar where I believed he was with his friends. During this encounter, I made a remark about obtaining a gun, even though it was a baseless threat, as I do not own a gun or have any means to acquire one. Looking back, I understand that this was a foolish and inappropriate statement to make.

During the altercation, I admit to slapping my boyfriend across the face. Although I recognize that my actions were inappropriate, I want to clarify that I did not cause any further harm during the incident. I deeply regret my behavior and the distress it may have caused.

I acknowledge that my actions were not the best way to handle the situation and that my behavior must have disturbed others at the bar. I take full responsibility for the fear and unease I may have imposed upon them that evening. I sincerely apologize for the disturbance caused.

Your Honor, I come before the court today, fully aware of the gravity of my actions, and I accept the consequences that come with this guilty plea. However, I would like to stress that this incident should not define me. I have no prior criminal record and, as part of my efforts towards personal growth, I am already attending therapy sessions on a weekly basis to address my emotional well-being.

I humbly request the court's leniency and understanding as I strive to learn from this experience and become a better person.

Thank you for your attention.
