Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, appear before you today to accept responsibility and plead guilty to the offense of affray. I deeply regret my actions and the discomfort I caused to those present at the bar.

After discovering that my boyfriend had been unfaithful, I experienced a surge of emotions that clouded my judgment. I made the ill-advised decision to confront him at the bar where he was with his friends. During our encounter, I expressed my anger by threatening to acquire a gun, although it is essential to clarify that I have no access to firearms.

In the heat of the moment, I impulsively slapped my boyfriend across the face. I want to emphasize that I did not inflict any further harm upon him during the incident. While I recognize that my actions were inappropriate, I deeply regret my behavior and the distress it may have caused.

I acknowledge that my conduct was not the best way to handle the situation, and I accept full responsibility for the fear and anxiety I may have caused to others present at the bar. I unreservedly apologize for the disturbance I created.

I stand before this court today, fully aware of the gravity of my actions, and willingly accept the consequences associated with my guilty plea. With an otherwise unblemished criminal record, I regularly attend therapy sessions once a week as part of my ongoing commitment to personal growth and emotional well-being.

I kindly request the court's understanding and leniency as I sincerely endeavor to learn from this experience and become a more responsible individual.

Thank you for your time and consideration.
