Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, come before you today to acknowledge my responsibility and plead guilty to the charge of affray. I deeply regret my actions and the distress I caused to those present at the bar.

After learning of my boyfriend's infidelity, I was overwhelmed by a surge of emotions which led me to make several regrettable choices. During our encounter at the bar, driven by a combination of anger and hurt, I reacted inappropriately by threatening him with a firearm, despite not possessing one or having any means to obtain one.

In the heat of the moment, I admittedly lost control and slapped my boyfriend across the face. I want to emphasize that at no point did I inflict any further harm upon him during the incident. Nonetheless, I recognize that this physical act was entirely unacceptable.

I fully acknowledge that my behavior was not only inappropriate but also immature in handling the situation. I accept full responsibility for the fear and discomfort I may have caused to others present at the bar, and for this, I extend my sincere apologies.

Today, I stand before this honorable court accepting the gravity of my actions and willingly entering a guilty plea. The act of pleading guilty demonstrates my acknowledgment of my wrongdoing and serves as a testament to my sincere remorse.

It is important to note that prior to this incident, I have maintained a clean criminal record. Furthermore, I am already actively engaged in personal growth and healing. I currently attend therapy sessions once a week to address and work on my emotional well-being.

I humbly request the court's understanding and leniency as I demonstrate my genuine commitment to learn from this experience and evolve into a more responsible and accountable individual.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

